{
  "stem": "2581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They came constantly in the ghetto to rob whatever they-- they-- they could.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was getting from bad to worse.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There weren't really many people left to be sent away to the-- work-- people in working-- working-- working condition.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Till they came to the-- you know-- there was, in two years, there isn't so much time spent to notice how this thing, you know, these things go from bad to-- but they did.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "People lost-- lost members of their family.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And in '42, they came in Octo-- August on the 24th.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they deported everyone from our home-- from our hometown.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And those that didn't go to the Lodz Ghetto were sent to Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother and my brother and most of those people in our town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And when I went in 1945, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think it was August.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We went for yahrzeit.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Jews left at that time and those that came to-- from other-- from other places to Lask, we all fit-- in a truck.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not in a truck.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was only halfway filled.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we came to-- to Chelmno to  say Kaddish [? over there. ?] Well, you can imagine in 1945 when the wounds were so fresh and everyone was missing everyone, what was going on there by that Kaddish.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I walked around and I saw these burned pieces of bones laying shattered around, all over the place.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I put them in a-- in a piece of paper.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I collected them and I took them with me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And later on, when I was already back in Germany, I gave these bones to this rabbi-- our rabbi.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The rabbi that I mentioned before that he was hung and let down.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Their son lived in Israel.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So he came to visit to Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
